1.00	Shakira_(singer)	Shakira	Shakira Isabel Mebarak Ripoll ( , Spanish: ; born February 2, 1977), known mononymously as Shakira, is a Colombian singer-songwriter who emerged in the music scene of Colombia and Latin America in the early 1990s. Born and raised in Barranquilla, Colombia, Shakira began performing in school, demonstrating her vocal ability with rock and roll, Latin and Arabic influences with her own original twist on belly dancing. Shakira is a native Spanish speaker and also speaks fluent English and Portuguese as well as some Italian, French, Catalan and Arabic.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7f/Shakira.JPG/220px-Shakira.JPG
